communicated by:
ProMED
<promed@promedmail.org>

[A large number of fungal, bacterial, viral, and nematode pathogens are known to affect capsicum (including chilli varieties) and related solanaceous crops. The insect pests mentioned above are common vectors of viruses. Yellowing symptoms, as mentioned above, are very unspecific and may be caused by many different pathogens as well as insects or external factors or combinations of any of these. Reliable diagnosis is vital to provide management strategies but may be problematic within the country, considering the absence of molecular diagnostic facilities stated above. Diagnostic services are available internationally to receive samples for confirmation and may need to be used.

